https://www.altexsoft.com/blog/non-functional-requirements/

"Performance. How fast does the system return results?

Scalability. How much will performance change with higher workloads?

Portability. Which hardware, operating systems, and browsers, along with their versions, does the software run on?

Compatibility. Does the system conflict with other applications and processes?

Reliability. How often does the system experience critical failures?

Maintainability.  How much time does it take to fix the issue when it arises?

Availability. How long is the average system downtime?

Security. How well are the system and its data protected against attacks?

Usability. How easy is it to use the system?"


https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/software-engineering/functional-vs-non-functional-requirements/

Scalability
-> Number of users platform can handle

Portability
-> Deployment on docker + cloud

Compatibility
-> This is regarding multiple browsers if we're doing that

Reliability
-> Storing, managing, retrieving user profiles, booking data and message history

Availability
-> Must be up and running type thing to avoid missed bookings, messages, etc. 

Maintainability
-> Would think the code should be fairly modular for easy fixes + version control technically

Security
-> Encrypted passwords and Paypal authentication?

Usability
-> User friendly UI

Performance
-> Maybe mention something along how long it takes to move from page to page 

